{{Otheruses|Sexagenary cycle|西涼の元号|庚子 (西涼)}}


{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}


'''Yang Metal Rat also known as 庚子''' (kanoene, koukin no nezumi, koukin no ne, koushi) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 37th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Kihai|ja|己亥}} and followed by {{ill|Shinchuu|ja|辛丑}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Kou|ja|庚|1=Kanoe (庚)}} represents yang {{ill|Metal|ja|金}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Rat|ja|子 (十二支)|lt=Rat|lt_ja=子}} represents yang {{ill|Water|ja|水}}, establishing a generating relationship ({{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|五行思想#相生（そうじょう）|lt=Mutual Generation|lt_ja=相生}}) (Metal generates Water).  
==Yang Metal Rat (庚子)'s Years==
