In a {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=西暦|4=zh|5=公元|6=es|7=Era común|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} year whose final digit is 1 or 6 (when the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} are {{ill|Sin|ja|辛|1=Kanoto (辛)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} and {{ill|Hei|ja|丙|1=Hinoe (丙)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}), the month of {{ill|November|ja|11月|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} is designated as the {{ill|month (calendar)|ja|月 (暦)|lt=Month|lt_ja=月|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} of {{ill|Koushi|ja|庚子|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}. However, here the term "month" may refer either to the month of the {{ill|Lunisolar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} or to the seasonal month (from {{ill|Heavy Snow|ja|大雪|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} until the day before {{ill|Lesser Cold|ja|小寒|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}) as applicable.

